COPY ~%MOD_FOLDER%/2da/bubb~ ~override~

COPY_EXISTING ~C0WL00X.SPL~ ~OVERRIDE~
SAY NAME1 ~Deactivate Blast Shape~
SAY UNIDENTIFIED_DESC ~Deactivate the currently equipped blast shape.~
COPY_EXISTING ~C0WL101.SPL~ ~OVERRIDE~
WRITE_BYTE 0x1C 3
WRITE_BYTE 0x34 10
LPF ADD_SPELL_CFEFFECT INT_VAR opcode = 171 target = 1 timing = 1 STR_VAR resource = C0WL101 END
LPF ADD_SPELL_CFEFFECT INT_VAR opcode = 172 target = 1 timing = 1 STR_VAR resource = C0WL101 END
SAY NAME1 ~^0xFFC76771^-Eldritch Blast~
SAY UNIDENTIFIED_DESC ~ELDRITCH BLAST: A warlock attacks <PRO_HISHER> foes with Eldritch power, using baleful magical energy to deal damage and sometimes impart other debilitating effects. An Eldritch Blast deals 1d6 points of magical damage at 1st level and increases by 1d6 in power for every three levels gained (up to 14d6 at 40th level). The default blast shape has a casting time of 1, while advanced blast shapes have longer casting times. The blast is treated as a ranged attack, and the regular shape can critically strike, inflicting damage and additional effects twice. There is no Saving Throw against this attack, but Magic Resistance can negate it.

As the warlock gains in levels, <PRO_HESHE> is able to shape <PRO_HISHER> Eldritch Blast into different forms.
	3rd level: HIDEOUS BLOW: The first melee attack each round channels an Eldritch Blast.
	7th level: ELDRITCH SPEAR: Eldritch Blast penetrates through all enemies between the caster and target. Sets attacks per round to 1.
	9th level: ELDRITCH GLAIVE: Eldritch Blast is shaped into a melee weapon which deals blast damage in a small cone in front of the warlock.
	11th level: ELDRITCH CHAIN: Eldritch Blast chains to one extra target per 3 levels, dealing 1d6 reduced damage per target. Sets attacks per round to 1.
	15th level: ELDRITCH CONE: Eldritch Blast takes the shape of a 90-degree cone. Increases casting time by 4.
	19th level: ELDRITCH DOOM: Eldritch Blast affects all enemies within a 15-ft. radius of the caster. Increases casting time by 6.~
COPY_EXISTING ~C0WL102.SPL~ ~OVERRIDE~
WRITE_BYTE 0x1C 3
WRITE_BYTE 0x34 10
LPF ADD_SPELL_CFEFFECT INT_VAR opcode = 171 target = 1 timing = 1 STR_VAR resource = C0WL102 END
LPF ADD_SPELL_CFEFFECT INT_VAR opcode = 172 target = 1 timing = 1 STR_VAR resource = C0WL102 END
